Package command.elements

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    UndoRedoStatusListener
    Listener for changes in the 'undo enabled' and 'redo enabled' status.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GraphicElementAddShapeCommand
    Command which adds a given shape to a graphic element.
    GraphicElementCommand
    A command specialized for graphic element related functionality, as that subsystem supports undo and redo of commands.
    GraphicElementCompositeCommand
    GraphicElementCommand representing the composition of zero or more GraphicElementCommands, which are undone and redone as a single unit.
    GraphicElementCopyCommand
    Command to copy the current selection to the clipboard.
    GraphicElementCutCommand
    Command which cuts the current selection to the clipboard.
    GraphicElementEditCancelCommand
    Command to revert the state of a graphic element, happening when the user cancels an edit operation.
    GraphicElementEditCommitCommand
    Command to commit the new state of a graphic element, happening when the user finishes an edit operation.
    GraphicElementInvoker
    Command invoker for graphic element related commands, supporting undo and redo with a fixed maximum history size.
    GraphicElementMoveShapeCommand
    Command which moves a given shape to a new position.
    GraphicElementPasteCommand
    Command that pastes the current clipboard contents to a graphic element.
    GraphicElementRemoveShapeCommand
    Command which removes a shape from a graphic element.
    TextElementEditCancelCommand
    Command which reverts the state of a text element to the one before an edit operation.
    TextElementEditCommitCommand
    Command which commits the new state of a text element after a confirmed edit operation.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    UndoUnsupportedException
    Exception thrown when undoing a particular command is not implemented.
